article.headline: Murray St. 70, Morehead St. 67
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Murray State junior guard Bruce Carter scored 14 points and hauled down 11 rebounds as the Racers defeated Morehead State 70-67 on Saturday. Murray State (4-7, 2-1 Ohio Valley Conference) led 50-40 with 14 minutes left in the game to see Morehead State battle back. The Eagles (4-4, 1-1) tied the game at 63 and 65 before Rob Kennedys bucket put the Racers up for good. Kennedy also finished with 14 points while Tyler Holloway chipped in 11. Morehead State was topped by Shaun Williams' 19 points and 10 rebounds. Maze Stallworth had 14 points while Cordaryl Ballard and Quentin Pryor ended with 12 and 11 points, respectively. The Racers hit 25 of 49 from the field, including 6-of-12 3-point attempts, while Morehead State was 23-of-56, including 7-of-19 from 3-point range. The Eagles outrebounded the Racers 38-26.
